{
  "stem": "7739.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And most of the time, we came back either with some potatoes, and if the fruit was on the trees, they would let us take some fruit down.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And sometimes they used to take to them a bar of soap, or some salt that we still had leftover from the stock from the store, and we would exchange for flour or anything like this.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we would carry it back.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And this helped us out.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And of course, we had to share everything with these other families who had been so-called-- so invited to our house.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There was no such thing as privacy.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You couldn't eat on your own if you wanted to, you had to share everything.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We had a lot of Gentile friends, customers in the store.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And people who were supposed to hide out my brother, we gave them most of our possessions knowing that we wouldn't-- when the expulsion takes place, you will not-- we would not be able to take it with us.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So we gave them money, we gave them shirts, clothing, whatever we had, we gave it to them.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And this is what hurts me so much.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "When the day of the expulsion took place, which is every time I think of this, and I close my eyes, you know, I still shudder-- the such brutality that this took place, although we expected it more or less.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "You would see people being shot-- and these are not strange people.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Most people knew each other.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "You tried to go and help someone who was beaten up or shot, they would shoot you too, and beat you up.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So you could see-- you could see scenes under the people that haven't been there cannot imagine what took place.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
